x>-1
\lim_{x\to -1^+}\frac{\ln(2+x)}{1+x}=     \lim_{t\to\infty}\ln\left(1+\frac{1}{t}\right)^t=\ln e=1
1+x
-1/t
x<-1
\lim_{x\to -1^-}\frac{\ln(2+x)}{1+x}=     \lim_{t\to\infty}\ln\biggl(\biggl(1+\frac{-1}{t}\biggr)^t\,\biggr)^{-1}=\ln (e^{-1})^{-1}=1
